title: Canadian Olympic Committee president quits amid inquiry
text: > Sports Canadian Olympic Committee president quits amid inquiry FILE - In this July 27, 2012, file photo, Canadian Olympic Committee President Marcel Aubut speaks to reporters during a news conference for the 2012 Summer Olympics in London. Aubut has resigned as president of the Canadian Olympic Committee while under investigation for a sexual harassment complaint. The committee said in a statement Saturday, Oct. 3, 2015, its investigation now ends. Since the original complaint, two other women made allegations against Aubut. (Ryan Remiorz/The Canadian Press via AP, File) MANDATORY CREDIT
